# Security headers + rate limit + Turnstile

Source: `/docs/SECURITY.md` (when written) and `AGENTS.md §8`.

## CSP allowlist (production)

```
default-src 'self';
script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://js.stripe.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://*.clerk.accounts.dev https://clerk.<your-domain>;
style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline';
img-src 'self' data: blob: https://img.clerk.com https://*.stripe.com;
connect-src 'self' https://*.clerk.accounts.dev https://clerk.<your-domain> https://api.stripe.com https://*.ingest.sentry.io https://plausible.io https://*.upstash.io;
frame-src 'self' https://js.stripe.com https://hooks.stripe.com https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://*.clerk.accounts.dev;
font-src 'self' data:;
object-src 'none';
base-uri 'self';
form-action 'self' https://*.clerk.accounts.dev https://js.stripe.com;
frame-ancestors 'none';
upgrade-insecure-requests;
```

Apply via `next.config.js` headers function. Don't roll your own middleware for headers — Next 15 supports this natively.

Always also set:

- `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload`
- `X-Frame-Options: DENY`
- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`
- `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`
- `Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()`

## Rate limit

Wrapper lives in `src/lib/rate-limit/`. One file per surface:

```ts
// src/lib/rate-limit/verify-card.ts (Patch-08)
// src/lib/rate-limit/server-action.ts (default 30/min per user)
// src/lib/rate-limit/sign-up.ts (5/h per IP)
```

Wrappers fail closed: on Upstash unreachable, return `{ success: false }`. Documented in RUNBOOK §10.x — do not "improve" this to fail open.

## Turnstile

Server verification in `src/lib/captcha/turnstile.ts`:

```ts
import "server-only";

export type TurnstileResult =
  | { ok: true }
  | { ok: false; reason: "INVALID_TOKEN" | "EXPIRED" | "NETWORK" };

export async function verifyTurnstile(token: string, remoteIp?: string): Promise<TurnstileResult> {
  // POST to https://challenges.cloudflare.com/turnstile/v0/siteverify
  // body: { secret, response: token, remoteip: remoteIp }
  // Return discriminated result; never throw.
}
```

Turnstile required on:

- Sign-up form.
- Password reset form (when implemented).
- `/verify-card` lookup form.
- Any future public-facing form that hits DB.

Not required on:

- Sign-in (Clerk handles its own bot defense).
- Stripe webhooks (signature-verified, not user input).

